<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06037c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06037c">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06037c"> 37(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ to the lightning of heaven</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[From a poem-translation by J.J. Callanan, &lsquo;The Convict of Clonmell&rsquo;, relating the melancholy execution of a hurley-player]</font> &mdash; <br>No boy in the village <br>Was ever yet milder, <br>I&apos;d play with a child, <br>And my sport would be wilder. <br>I&apos;d dance without tiring <br>From morning till even, <br>And the goal-ball I&apos;d strike <br><mark>To the lightning of Heaven</mark>. <small> W.B. Yeats, <a name="YEATS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#YEATS"><cite title="source">A Book of Irish Verse</cite></a> (1900) 18</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
